      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 1519: `cameraFlip()` resets only the fragment\u0027s cached zoom. Because `CameraService` stores zoom per camera id and reapplies it in `applyZoom()`, switching back to a previously zoomed camera can unexpectedly restore the old zoom while `currentCameraZoom` is 1f. Reset the active camera zoom through the hardware service before/after switching, or clear zoom state in `CameraService.switchInput()` for the newly selected camera.",
