      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 690: The pre-Android R crop region ignores `SENSOR_INFO_ACTIVE_ARRAY_SIZE.left/top`. Active arrays are not guaranteed to start at `(0, 0)`, so this can produce an invalid or shifted crop on some devices. Offset the crop by the active rect origin:\n```suggestion\nval left \u003d active.left + (active.width() - w) / 2\nval top \u003d active.top + (active.height() - h) / 2\nbuilder.set(CaptureRequest.SCALER_CROP_REGION, Rect(left, top, left + w, top + h))\n```",
